##############################################################
Creating PR:
	1. Creat and checkout to local_work_branch
	( 'git checkout -b bugfix/FI-1212')
	2. Add changes to local branch
	3. Make git pull(to update local branch with master)
	4. Check 'git status' and 'git diff'
	5. Then 'git add file_name' (files u have modified,each file in separate cmd)
	6. 'git commit' ---> opens file there add defect ID and comments,summary
	7. 'git push origin local_branch'
#################################################################
git cheery-pick commit-id
#################################################################
Adding and removing previous commit:

Git add
Git commit --amend
Git push --force origin bugfix/branch

##################################################################
Git fetch --> This shows what new changes are made to the current local directory  to compare with remote repo

Git pull --> it does git fetch and also copies all the new changes that showed in the git fetch.
Git fetch

Manually doing merge confilits
From your private branch do:=Git pull origin master
##################################################################
Cloneing a specific branch in git:-

Git clone -b <branch> <remote-repo>
##################################################################
Git branch name changes:

Git branch -m New_name [Changes current branch name]

###################################################################
Discard local changes in git
1. git reset --hard
git clean -fxd  or git pull

####################################################################
# Checkout the desired branch
git checkout <branch>
# Undo the desired commit
git revert <commit>
# Update the remote with the undo of the code
# The force is a tricky flag since it will force the push but
# your administrator can block it, so if it's not an option you
# can delete the old branch and push it again
git push origin <branch> --force

